02/13/85 deroute

Syntax as a command:  deroute source stream old_vcons


Function:  removes a virtual console from a specified source.  This
command can be used in ring 4.


Arguments:
source
   is the name of the source of output.
stream
   is the name of the stream on which output is being carried.
old_vcons
   is the name of the virtual console to be removed from the output
   list.


Notes:  If the stream is left with no virtual consoles, output is sent
to the default virtual console, which is usually defined to be the
bootload console.
